# Cursor Rules Index

Quick reference guide to help AI assistants locate and apply the right rules for any task.

---

## All Rules Overview

| Rule File                       | Purpose                                                                 | When to Use                                                          | Always Applied |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------- |
| **implementation-workflow.mdc** | Mandatory workflow: research → clarify → propose → approve → implement  | **CRITICAL**: Start here for ANY implementation task                 | ✅ Yes         |
| **pre-production.mdc**          | Pre-production guidelines: update migrations, no backward compatibility | **IMPORTANT**: Database changes, breaking changes, refactoring       | ✅ Yes         |
| **index.mdc**                   | Quick reference index of all rules                                      | Routing table for finding the right rule                             | ✅ Yes         |
| **nest-js.mdc**                 | NestJS patterns, architecture, database, repositories, RBAC, entitlements | Working with modules, controllers, services, repositories, DTOs, entitlements | 🔄 On demand  |
| **project-structure.mdc**       | Complete project navigation and file organization                       | Finding files, understanding directory structure, locating modules   | 🔄 On demand  |
| **technology-stack.mdc**        | Dependencies, versions, compatibility, best practices                   | Adding dependencies, checking versions, understanding tech decisions | 🔄 On demand  |
| **self-improvement.mdc**        | When and how to update rules                                            | After significant implementations, checking if rules need updating   | 🔄 On demand  |
| **testing.mdc**                 | Testing conventions, integration test patterns, factories, helpers       | Writing tests, creating factories/helpers, modifying test infra      | 🔄 On demand  |
| **cursor-rules.mdc**            | How to create and manage Cursor rules                                   | Creating new rules, understanding rule structure                     | 🔄 On demand  |

