## Quick Task Reference

| Task Type                     | Primary Rules                                                           | Action                                                        |
| ----------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Any Implementation**        | `implementation-workflow.mdc` → then others                             | ALWAYS start here - defines mandatory workflow                |
| **Database Changes**          | `pre-production.mdc` + `nest-js.mdc`                                    | Update existing migrations, no backward compatibility needed  |
| **Breaking Changes**          | `pre-production.mdc` + `implementation-workflow.mdc`                    | Make changes freely, update docs and tests                    |
| **Adding Feature/Module**     | `implementation-workflow.mdc` + `nest-js.mdc` + `project-structure.mdc` | Research patterns, follow NestJS conventions, check structure |
| **Implementing Entitlements** | `implementation-workflow.mdc` + `nest-js.mdc` (Entitlement section)     | Check entitlement patterns, use EntitlementGuard, sync service |
| **Fixing Bugs**               | `implementation-workflow.mdc` + `project-structure.mdc` + `nest-js.mdc` | Research first, locate files, understand patterns             |
| **Adding Dependencies**       | `implementation-workflow.mdc` + `technology-stack.mdc`                  | Check existing stack, verify compatibility                    |
| **Writing Tests**             | `testing.mdc` + `nest-js.mdc`                                           | Follow test conventions, use factories, update test docs      |
| **Navigating Codebase**       | `project-structure.mdc`                                                 | Find files, understand organization                           |
| **Creating Rules**            | `cursor-rules.mdc` + `self-improvement.mdc`                             | Follow rule format, check when to add                         |

